node.text:
Circuit breaker day 38: First attempt at beef horfun for the family (cos I don't take beef ).👩‍🍳
🔸️
One likes it dry and the other likes it with gravy, so made it semi-dry with some gravy. 😉
🔸️
Another day to Friday! Jiayou! 💪

#circuitbreaker #sgunited #stayhomesg
@mightymousie Thanks Jane! Luckily turned out ok as I can't even try or taste with beef in it 😅😉
@xxoo_cin I eat Liao lo!!!! I whacked my lunch in 10 min😝😝
@thekitchenettetales That was quick .. can imagaine how hungry you were 😅
@35sweetpotato 🙌 Thanks! Glad it turn out fine for a non-beef person to cook this 😅
Looks good 😍. I don’t take beef too 🤣
@jennychee.ly Thanks Jenny! 😉 I love horfun too, except beef 😅
@khoosl_eve Thanks Eve! 🤗 I totally don't take beef. When frying the beef gravy, it was all based on estimation and I can try if seasonings are fine 😅
@xxoo_cin You still managed to whip up a very nice dish
Looks good! I rarely eat beef either and when I do, I’ll take probably a mouthful or two at most
@eatandtravelwithus Thanks for the kind words.. but I did made one for myself, without beef 😅
Wow not bad!! So nice of u to cook even though u don’t eat! 😊👍🏻❤️
@cookwithsusan Thanks Susan. First time see semi-dry. It looks so lacking in gravy in the pic 😅😅
Yummy. Just made horfun too. Yours is perfect for semi-dry 👍💕
@omtasteofnepal.worthing.uk Thank you for the kind words 🤗😘
@sixpmfooddiary Wet ones, I will need extra eggs in the gravy! 😘😘
Looks great! I like mine wet 🤤
Looks great and a nice compromise!
@pigeats.balltravels Indeed! All seasonings are based on estimation 😅😅
Haha must be difficult to cook sth without being able to taste it!😆
@flavourforager All I did was fry the horfun in high heat, and coat them with black soy sauce.
Hot fun is my fave. I’d love to know how to do wok hei
